# EmailJS Configuration (Example)
# Replace these with your actual keys from the EmailJS dashboard.

# Service ID from "Email Services" tab
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id_here

# Template ID from "Email Templates" tab
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_template_id_here

# Public Key from "Account" > "API Keys"
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here

# --- TEMPLATE SETUP INSTRUCTIONS ---
# In your EmailJS template, use the following variables:
# {{from_name}} - The sender's full name
# {{from_email}} - The sender's email address
# {{subject}} - The message subject
# {{message}} - The message body
# {{date_time}} - When the message was sent
#
# IMPORTANT: Set the "Reply-To" field in your EmailJS template settings to: {{from_email}}
